-Practices priority settings and resource management of the department resources, aligned with business needs
-Actively planning potential CAPEX investments in field of warehouse facility improvements, capacity expansions, maintenance overhauls
-Oversee SCM project-based work 
-Contribute to cost saving strategies including work methodologies and energy saving ideas;
-Internal and external audits support on SCM part;
-Undertake and document a termly risk assessment of the whole site and other risk assessments/ health and safety checks; 
-Maintain legislative and regulatory documentation to exceed audit requirements; 
-Assure that all safety and environmental laws and rules are adhered
-Other tasks assigned.

Supply Chain management
-Manage the development of logistics/supply chain policies and procedures, using market knowledge and benchmark results to ensure that they reflect the best practices;
-Improve the efficiency of logistics/supply chain processes and prevent any interruption of customers’ production process for shortage of parts;
-Supervise customer orders processing with maximum efficiency at minimum costs from a freight standpoint (freight optimization and timely delivery);
-Undertake ownership over the demand, material and supply planning 
-Insure in time supply of raw material/ packaging materials, etc, for production, based on production needs/ consumption;
-Maintain the inventory levels in accordance with the policies adopted and consistent with the regular and timely supply to the company’s operation, as well as to establish the control of goods in stocks, so as to eliminate losses, waste and pilferage;
-Coordinate and control all warehouse and packaging activities;
-Development and implementation of a standardized packaging in regard with all finished goods;
-Instruct and coordinate the work concerning the shipping of finished products to customers, using adequate packing, count and storage processes and internal requirements from production based on daily/ weekly consumption;
-Develop, run and manage the freight contracts and Logistics services provided by third parties;
-Coordinate and control transportation (freight –in and –out for the purpose of achieving the on time delivery and complying with the delivery terms set forth, through the rational use of the resources available in Logistics;
-Manage logistic claims and execute case analysis and cause rectification;
-Conduct the negotiation, licensing and IMPEX customs clearances with trade associations and governmental agencies;
-Provide advice in all the aspects of finished product supply to the management team;
-Other tasks assigned.

 Position Qualification &amp; Requirements
-Bachelor degree or above majored in Supply Chain, Operations Management, or relevant field;
